        x.innerHTML = "<div class='text-center'><h3><b>Ingl√©s</b></h3></div><br><div class='container'><p style='text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-word'>La <b>prueba de ingl√©s</b> est√° a√∫n por determinar ya que se acaban de a√±adir una serie de preguntas de <b>comprensi√≥n de textos</b>. Hasta ahora consist√≠a en un examen de <b>gram√°tica inglesa</b> de <b>20 preguntas</b> tipo <b>test</b> con <b>4 opciones</b> a elegir. Adem√°s, hab√≠a que contestar <b>1 pregunta</b> de <b>reserva</b> en un tiempo total de <b>21 min</b>. El nivel de los <b>contenidos</b> a evaluar corresponde al programa de <b>ESO</b> descrito en el Real Decreto 1105/2014 siendo los contenidos los siguientes:</p><ul class='nu'><li>Condicional 1: <b>if</b> (si).&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class='forSm'><br style='content:close-quote'></span>Ej: <b>If</b> you study, you will pass the exam.</li><li>Condicional 2: <b>if</b> (si).&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class='forSm'><br style='content:close-quote'></span>Ej: <b>If</b> I won the lottery, I would buy a big house.</li><li>Condicional 3: <b>if</b> (si).&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class='forSm'><br style='content:close-quote'></span>Ej: <b>If</b> I hadn't eaten so much, I wouldn't have felt sick.</li><li>Condici√≥n: <b>unless</b> (a menos que).&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class='forSm'><br style='content:close-quote'></span>Ej: You'll be sick <b>unless</b> you stop eating.</li><li>Estilo indirecto: <b>informaci√≥n rese√±ada</b>.&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class='forSm'><br style='content:close-quote'></span>Ej: <b>Did James tell you how old he is?</b></li><li>Estilo indirecto: <b>peticiones</b>.&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class='forSm'><br style='content:close-quote'></span>Ej: She <b>asked for</b> an apple.</li><li>Estilo indirecto: <b>sugerencias</b>.&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class='forSm'><br style='content:close-quote'></span>Ej: She <b>suggested</b> I see the doctor.</li><li>Estilo indirecto: <b>√≥rdenes</b>.&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class='forSm'><br style='content:close-quote'></span>Ej: The doctor <b>told me to stop smoking</b>.</li><li><b>What a</b> + adj. + noun.&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class='forSm'><br style='content:close-quote'></span>Ej: <b>What a</b> wonderful ice-cream!</li><li><b>What</b> + adj. + noun.&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class='forSm'><br style='content:close-quote'></span>Ej: <b>What</b> wonderful funiture!</li><li><b>How</b> + adj. + noun.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class='forSm'><br style='content:close-quote'></span>Ej: <b>How</b> interesting!</li><li>Frases y oraciones <b>exclamativas</b>.&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class='forSm'><br style='content:close-quote'></span>Ej: ‚ÄúWell, that is a surprise!‚Äù, ‚ÄúFine! Great!‚Äù</li><li>Frases negativas con <b>not</b> (no).&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class='forSm'><br style='content:close-quote'></span>Ej: That is <b>not</b> exactly what she told you.</li><li>Frases negativas con <b>never</b> (nunca).&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class='forSm'><br style='content:close-quote'></span>Ej: She‚Äôs <b>never</b> been abroad.</li><li>Frases negativas con <b>no</b> (ning√∫n, nadie).&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class='forSm'><br style='content:close-quote'></span>Ej: <b>no</b> problem, <b>no</b>body, <b>no</b>where.</li><li>Frases negativas con <b>nothing</b> (nada).&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class='forSm'><br style='content:close-quote'></span>Ej: There‚Äôs <b>nothing</b> wrong with you.</li><li><b>Positive question tags</b> (¬øno?, ¬øverdad?).&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class='forSm'><br style='content:close-quote'></span>Ej: Pablo doesn‚Äôt work in a bank, <b>does he</b>?</li><li><b>Negative question tags</b> (¬øno?, ¬øverdad?).&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class='forSm'><br style='content:close-quote'></span>Ej: You are a student, <b>aren‚Äôt you?</b></li><li><b>Neither</b> (tampoco, ninguno).&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class='forSm'><br style='content:close-quote'></span>Ej: <b>neither</b> would I (yo tampoco), <b>neither</b> of them (ninguno de ellos).</li><li>Preposiciones <b>since</b> y <b>for</b> con present perfect.&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class='forSm'><br style='content:close-quote'></span>Ej: She has lived here <b>for twenty</b> years/<b>since</b> 2000.</li><li><b>Pasivas</b> (diferentes tiempos verbales).&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class='forSm'><br style='content:close-quote'></span>Ej: My father <b>bought</b> the house. The house <b>was bought by</b> my father.</li><li>Expresi√≥n de intenci√≥n futura: <b>present continuous</b>. &nbsp;&nbsp;<span class='forSm'><br style='content:close-quote'></span>Ej: <b>I‚Äôm meeting</b> John <b>on Saturday</b> to watch the football match.</li><li>Expresi√≥n de la <b>existencia</b>.&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class='forSm'><br style='content:close-quote'></span>Ej: <b>there will be</b> (habr√°), <b>there has been</b> (ha habido).</li><li>Expresi√≥n habitual: simple tenses + adv.&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class='forSm'><br style='content:close-quote'></span>Ej: <b>usually</b>, <b>always</b>, <b>used to</b>‚Ä¶</li><li>Expresi√≥n incoativa: <b>start -ing</b>, <b>be about to</b>.&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class='forSm'><br style='content:close-quote'></span>Ej: When shall I <b>start working?</b></li><li>Expresi√≥n terminativa: <b>stop -ing</b>.&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class='forSm'><br style='content:close-quote'></span>Ej: It‚Äôs <b>stopped raining</b>. Let‚Äôs go for a walk.</li><li><b>Affirmative tags</b> (part√≠culas afirmativas).&nbsp;&nbsp;<span class='forSm'><br style='content:close-quote'></span>Ej: 'I love travelling around the world.' '<b>So do I</b>.'</li><li><b>Have you</b> just <b>finished</b>?</li><li><b>Have</b> you <b>ever worked</b>?</li><li>Resultado: <b>so that</b> (as√≠ que).</li><li>Preguntas: <b>whose</b>, <b>where</b>, <b>what</b>, <b>who</b>, <b>whom</b> y <b>why</b>.</li><li>Expresi√≥n de capacidad: <b>can</b> y <b>be able</b>.</li><li>Expresi√≥n de posibilidad/probabilidad: <b>may</b>, <b>might</b> y <b>perhaps</b>.</li><li>Expresi√≥n de permiso: <b>may</b>, <b>could</b> y <b>allow</b>.</li><li>Expresi√≥n de necesidad: <b>must</b>, <b>need</b>, <b>have (got) to</b>.</li><li>Expresi√≥n de obligaci√≥n: <b>have</b> (got) <b>to</b>, <b>must</b>, <b>impera