uous</b> + <b>adv</b>. (con valor de <b>futuro</b>).</li><li>Expresi√≥n del tiempo futuro: <b>Will there be</b> a meeting‚Ä¶? (¬øHabr√°‚Ä¶?); <b>It will be</b> 3 in the afternoon (Ser√°n las 3).</li><li>Expresi√≥n del aspecto puntual: <b>simple tenses</b>. <span class='forSm'><br style='content:close-quote'></span>Ej: Last night, I ate a sandwich, but I didn't drink a beer.</li><li>Expresi√≥n del aspecto durativo: <b>present simple</b>, <b>present perfect</b>, <b>past simple</b>, <b>past perfect y future continuous</b>.<span class='forSm'><br style='content:close-quote'></span><span class='forLg'><br style='content:close-quote'></span>Ej: I lived in London for 4 years <b>but now</b> I live in Valencia).</li><li><b>Relative pronouns</b> (que, el que, quien, a quien, donde, cuando, lo que), <b>reflexive pronouns</b> (yourself), <b>emphatic pronouns</b> (yourself), <b>possessive determiners</b> (my), <b>possessive pronouns</b> (mine), <b>one</b>(s) (this one).</li><li>Expresi√≥n de la cualidad: <span class='forSm'><br style='content:close-quote'></span>Ej: <b>good at maths</b> (bueno en matem√°ticas), <b>rather tired</b> (bastante cansado).</li><li>Expresi√≥n de la cantidad: <b>singular</b> (apple), <b>plural</b> (apples), <b>cardinal numbers</b> (one), <b>ordinal numerals</b> (first), <b>the</b>, <b>a/an</b>, <b>both</b> (ambos), <b>none</b> (ninguno), <b>any</b>, <b>some</b>, <b>all</b>, <b>either</b>, <b>either of</b> you (cualquiera de vosotros), <b>none of</b> them (ninguno de ellos), <b>most</b> of them (la mayor√≠a de ellos), <b>really</b>, <b>quite</b>, <b>a little</b>, <b>so</b>, <b>enough</b> (enough money / beautiful enough), <b>too many</b>, <b>too</b>, <b>too much</b>.</li><li>Expresi√≥n del espacio: <b>away</b>, <b>off</b>, <b>apart</b>, <b>from</b>, <b>away from</b>, <b>from</b>‚Ä¶<b>to</b>.</li><li>Expresi√≥n de movimiento: <b>on foot, by bus</b>‚Ä¶</li><li>Expresi√≥n de direcci√≥n: <b>across</b>, <b>along</b>, <b>back</b>, <b>back to</b>, <b>down</b>, 